President Obama will be participating in a LinkedIn Town Hall event in Mountain View, California on September 26th. The event, titled "Putting America Back to Work: LinkedIn Presents a Town Hall with President Obama," will focus on job creation and the economy. The President will answer questions from a live audience consisting of LinkedIn members and employees, as well as questions submitted by LinkedIn members nationwide. LinkedIn has also launched a community dedicated to job creation and the economy, where users can submit questions for the town hall, share content, and engage with the White House and Administration officials. The event will be livestreamed on LinkedIn and WhiteHouse.gov/live. LinkedIn, with over 120 million members worldwide, will provide a platform for a diverse range of individuals, including small business owners, employees, community college students, and veterans, to voice their concerns and ideas to President Obama.